  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "While there have been efforts to develop parsers capable of handling longer text spans, most AMR parsers remain focused on sentence-level parsing.",
    "Furthermore, although AMR was not initially designed for non-English languages, several approaches have been proposed to extend its capabilities to multilingual parsing.AMRs have continued to evolve over time, with various extensions and enrichment strategies being introduced.",
    "One notable extension is Uniform Meaning Representation (UMR) [104], which aims to support cross-linguistic plausibility and portability.",
    "UMRs are currently a focus of active research, and it is possible that they could eventually replace traditional AMRs in some applications.Text generation from AMRs is another domain of active research discussed in this survey.",
    "This task focuses on generating corresponding text from an AMR while preserving the semantic integrity of the original input."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "One notable extension is Uniform Meaning Representation (UMR) [104], which aims to support cross-linguistic plausibility and portability."
  ]
